description.narrative: This Development Policy Support Program (DPSP-5) is the fifth in the programmatic series of annual single-tranche operations in Indonesia. It is a continuation of DPSPs 1-4. The DPSP series-cofinancing the Development Policy Loan (DPL) series supported by the World Bank and the Government of Japan-is embedded in the Government's Medium-Term National Development Plan (RPJM) for 2004-2009. It supports the RPJM's broad goals of stimulating higher and sustainable economic growth, with lower levels of unemployment and poverty, in three core areas: (i) investment climate, (ii) public financial management and governance, and (iii) poverty alleviation and public service delivery to the poor. DPSP-5 is also a single-tranche operation based on completed actions demonstrating satisfactory progress. It builds on reforms undertaken during past DPSPs and establishes policy actions for possible future operation.
